    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-24T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-24T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 24, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 24—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>285. Canton’s April 22, 4 p.m.<note n="96" xml:id="d70fn96">Not printed.</note>
                    Following has been sent to the Minister for Foreign Affairs: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The American Consul General at Canton reports that American
                            missionaries, who have just reached Canton from Southern Kiangsi, state
                            that at least 19 American missionaries are still in Kanchow unable to
                            leave and that the Communist forces are again converging on Kanchow
                            where the Americans are in grave danger.</p>
                        <p>It would be much appreciated if Your Excellency would be so food as to
                            make available to me any reliable information which may have been
                            received concerning present conditions at Kanchow.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Hankow and Canton informed.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
